
==Installation==

You will need:

 http://wiki.apertium.org/wiki/Trmorph

Use the instructions on the Wiki to download and compile. To make 
tr-mor.ol, run the following in the trmorph directory:

 hfst-invert -i trmorph.a | hfst-fst2fst -O -o tr-mor.ol

You need to make a symlink from the Turkish analyser:

 ln -s /path/to/tr-mor.ol tr-ky.automorf.hfst

Now run make:

 make

And test:

 echo "Ahmet okula gitti." | apertium -d . tr-ky-bil
^Ahmet<np>/Ахмет<np><ant><m>$ ^okul<n><dat>/мектеп<n><dat>$ 
 ^git<v><t_past><3s>/кет<v><t_past><3s>$.

===============================================================================

Here are the tagsets of Trmorph, the Turkish morphological analyser and Kymorph
the Kyrgyz morphological analyser compared:

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Trmorph		Kymorph		Description
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
<n>		<n>		Noun
<v>		<v>		Verb
<postp>		<post>		Postposition

<pl>		<pl>		Plural

<1s>		<sg1>		First person singular
<2s>		<sg2>		Second person singular

<p1s>		<px1sg>		Possessive, first person singular
<p2s>		<px2sg>		Possessive, second person singular

-		<nom>		Nominative / absolutive
<acc>		<acc>
<dat>		<dat>
<loc>		<loc>
<abl>		<abl>
<ins>		-
	

===============================================================================
